priate and stylistically varied outputs, positioning it as a significant contribution to controllable language modeling.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Baidu and Pengcheng Lab co-developed large-scale ERNIE models with knowledge integration\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Baidu, in collaboration with Pengcheng Lab, developed two advanced ERNIE models: ERNIE-ViLG 2.0 (10B parameters) and ERNIE 3.0 Titan (260B parameters). Both models are pretrained on English Wikipedia and Wikidata to enhance entity recognition and knowledge-intensive reasoning [Data: Entities (1178, 1179, 1180, 1181, 1150, 1174); Relationships (1854, 1856, 1849, 1851)]. The integration of structured knowledge from Wikidata allows these models to move beyond statistical language patterns and incorporate real-world conceptual relationships [Data: Entities (1174); Relationships (1856)]. First published in May 2019, these models represent a strategic effort by Chinese AI institutions to compete in the global landscape of large language models [Data: Entities (1193); Relationships (1872, 1873)]. Their scale and knowledge grounding make them notable for tasks requiring deep factual understanding.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"SeeKeR Dialogue models are trained on specialized conversational datasets\",\n            \"explanation\": \"The SeeKeR Dialogue models (with 400M and 3B parameters) are part of the SeeKeR family and are specifically pretrained on datasets tailored for dialogue and conversational AI. These include PersonaChat, Blended Skill Talk, Empathetic Dialogues, Multi-Session Chat, and MS MARCO [Data: Entities (1302, 1310, 1311, 1312, 1313, 1314); Relationships (2107, 2108, 2109, 2110, 2111)]. Additionally, SeeKeR Dialogue uses Wikipedia as part of its pretraining corpus, linking it to broader knowledge sources [Data: Relationships (2106)]. This focus on empathetic, multi-turn, and persona-consistent dialogue suggests that SeeKeR is optimized for 